						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Espozo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Something notable I found out too, is that Windows 95 through ME were I guess just GUIs for DOS, while 2000 and upwards are not. I'd have thought this would have made most every program developed for ME and earlier incompatible with 2000 and later, although maybe this was the case.<br /></div>That's ... really not true. Not by any reasonable stretch.<br /><br />Windows 1, 2, and 3 definitely were.<br /><br />But 95, 98, and ME had the properties of a &quot;real&quot; OS, even if it was one specifically designed for compatibility and performance rather than security. And although you could &quot;technically&quot; quit Windows 95/98 and get to a DOS prompt ... that really only meant that it knew how to put things back.</div>

